main event: An observer reported seeing a stationary saucer-shaped object in the western sky of Springhill, Kansas on March 5, 1967.
interesting points: The object was white with a bright orange glow around the bottom., The observation lasted for 15 minutes., The object did not float or dip but remained stationary., It was concluded that the object was likely the planet Venus based on its location in the sky., There was no physical evidence gathered during the sighting.
